Dear Forum Owners,

October is going to be another big month for Tapatalk developments. With the rollout of the redesigned app already underway, we have even more exciting features in the hopper for the spotlight before the year's out. We're also keen to hear your feedback on not only our mobile app but our various platform plugins as well while we fine tune the features users are already enjoying.

 

Tapatalk is Protected From Shellshock!

We have confirmed that Tapatalk is protected from the recent âShellshockâ bash bug that has been making waves in the news. Due to the webserver configuration of Tapatalkâs services, our exposure to shellshock was extremely limited, but just in case, our teams have implemented a couple of pre-emptive patches to ensure security against this exploit. 
https://sendy.tapatalk.com/l/lnf9dWOFRUETRyOdKyBf8Q/fAqE3N9wihOqtHLZeJBcMg/6RPeqRbdNHMP2ZoSRHppYA

While we are constantly on the lookout for security exploits ourselves, if you come across any security issues, we urge you to report them privately to us here via our Security Incident Response Team form. We appreciate any tips you may have that aid us in improving everyone's security on Tapatalk!


Meet Tapatalk's New Director of Infrastructure and Security

We are happy to announce that the founder of StopForumSpam, Paul Lush, has recently joined us full time as Tapatalk's new Director of Infrastructure and Security. He will be overseeing Tapatalk's infrastructure to bolster its robustness and security. Paul will also be helping us integrate some of the best features of StopForumSpam into Tapatalk and ensuring the implementation of best practices in spam prevention going forward.


A Friendlier Community Promotes Growth

One of Tapatalk's biggest goals is to provide an easy and enjoyable way for people to access the best forums online that match their interests. For many mainstream mobile users who may not be familiar with forums though, getting the hang of one may be a little daunting. We put together a quick guide that covers the basics of forum etiquette to help our readers skip the common mistakes newbies may make. Feel free to add more ideas in the comments, we'd love to hear from you!
https://sendy.tapatalk.com/l/lnf9dWOFRUETRyOdKyBf8Q/kzErWBTS7Wun2xZjTRXeQg/6RPeqRbdNHMP2ZoSRHppYA


Common Questions - Answered!

Wondering why that forum URL you just tried to register on Tapatalk is already taken? Accidentally made more than one account and need to move all your forums into one? These common questions and more can now be answered not only in our forums but also by logging into your Forum Owner Dashboard on our homepage. You may have noticed, once logged in and you have a forum selected, you can send us support tickets with your technical issues. However if you want to just chat, send us a private message on the forums . :)
https://sendy.tapatalk.com/l/lnf9dWOFRUETRyOdKyBf8Q/055ChCrYui55FQGdfZu9LA/6RPeqRbdNHMP2ZoSRHppYA

Thank You,

The Tapatalk Team


--b1_7fa3e23da2f39e734854b5b7affce0ad

Atlassian
www.atlassian.com

Important support policy changes

To better serve our customers and partners, Atlassian has modified our security policy for JIRA, Confluence, and Stash.

Atlassian Cloud customers are not affected by any of the changes described in this email as Cloud customers are always updated to the latest fixes and versions.

 - New policy for security fixes -

Under the new security policy, when fixes for critical security issues are identified, Atlassian will produce a new minor product release for all major versions of JIRA and Confluence released within the previous 12 months. Atlassian will also produce a new minor release for all major versions of Stash released within the prior 6 months.We are excited that Confluence will be able to support this new policy beginning with Confluence 5.5.

Our new policy not only extends our current security releases across more major application versions than our previous policy, but also offers these security fixes through full maintenance releases. Our prior policy only produced security fixes through binary patches and manual installation processes. Performing full maintenance releases for security fixes will ensure changes go through full regression testing and follow standard installation and support processes. For more details around our new security policy, read our updated Security Bugfix Policy:

http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdea15767d660d7b73117671&ls=fdf613747d65007d7717737c&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fe9915707d65067577&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ffcf14&t=

 - Updated end-of-life policy -

Atlassian is also announcing changes to its application end-of-life (EOL) policy today. Our previous policy defined the EOL date for a specific product release based on the last minor version release date. After speaking with our customers, we learned that this often made upgrade planning difficult because each major release was covered for a different length of time depending on the number of minor release versions. To provide our customers and partners a better and more consistent experience, Atlassian's policy will now associate an application's EOL date to the major release date.This will be identical for all products and is independent of how many minor releases, features, and bug
 fixes are performed.

Our goal is to provide a more simple, clear and consistent policy.All products will now have their EOL date set 2-years from the major release date and, to ensure a smooth transition for our customers, the new policy will not affect any previously published EOL dates for existing releases. For more details on the new EOL policy, read our Atlassian Support End of Life Policy:

http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fde915767d660d7b73117670&ls=fdf613747d65007d7717737c&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fe9915707d65067577&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ffcf14&t=
 
We're excited to bring these expanded and new service changes to our customers and partners.

Sincerely,

Bryan Mayo
Head of Enterprise Support,
Atlassian



This email was sent to keep you informed about changes to your products or accounts.

http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdff15777766057574177173&ls=fded13757660017a72107677&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec1167872600d7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff941374&t= 

Virtualized Agile 

Join us Tuesday, November 18th, 2014 at 11am PST:
http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdfd1577776605757417717d&ls=fded13757660017a72107677&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec1167872600d7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff941374&t= 

The Agile Manifesto states that face-to-face communication is the most efficient and effective method to communicate with and within an agile development team. But what if none of those team members sit in the same place, or even the same time zone? Can distributed agile teams deliver value, iteration after iteration, and rapidly adjust as customer needs and market conditions change? In short, can distributed teams reap the full benefits of agility?

Join us for the story of the evolution of Sonatype's distributed agile teams as told by Mike Hansen, Senior Vice President of Engineering, and Mark Kilby, Agile Coach. In this webinar you'll learn:
- Why distributed is a powerful differentiator
- How to foster a culture of collaboration
- Ways to overcome the pitfalls of distance

Atlassian

Cloud maintenance downtime

 Hello Lars , 
 
We have to perform some essential maintenance to your Cloud service (dri-jira.atlassian.net) which is outside of your regular maintenance windows:
http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdee15777164027c721d7873&ls=fde01374726c02747511797d&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec316717c6c0c7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff961677&t=

To try to minimize the impact of this maintenance, we have scheduled this downtime in the maintenance window listed below: 
 
  *  10:00 Sat 8 Nov &ndash; 14:00 Sun 8 Nov, Eastern time
  *  07:00 Sat 8 Nov &ndash; 11:00 Sat 8 Nov, Pacific time
  *  15:00 Sat 8 Nov &ndash; 19:00 Sat 8 Nov, Greenwich Mean time
  *  02:00 Sun 9 Nov &ndash; 06:00 Sun 9 Nov, Australian Eastern time
     All time zones: http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fded15777164027c721d7872&ls=fde01374726c02747511797d&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec316717c6c0c7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff961677&t=

You can watch this page to stay informed on what's coming up in Cloud:
http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdec15777164027c721d787d&ls=fde01374726c02747511797d&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec316717c6c0c7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff961677&t=

Or watch the Cloud maintenance windows page to receive updates about upcoming maintenance times:
http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdee15777164027c721d7873&ls=fde01374726c02747511797d&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec316717c6c0c7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff961677&t=

In the unlikely event you see any issues with your instance or data following the maintenance, please file a support ticket in the Cloud Support project:
http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdeb15777164027c721d787c&ls=fde01374726c02747511797d&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec316717c6c0c7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff961677&t=
 
Regards,

The Atlassian Cloud team

Webinar: Practical advice for agile product management 
November 12 Wednesday, 10am PST

Every product manager knows that great products start with great planning. At Atlassian, we take many different approaches to plan our releases, and in true agile fashion, we continue to refine and improve our process. 

Join two Atlassian product managers, Sherif Mansour and John Masson, as they share their experiences and the best practices they've honed over time for Agile Product Management. 

In this webinar, they will cover:

- Surveying and collecting product feedback
- Conducting and interpreting customer interviews
- Collaborating with development and marketing on product strategy
- Using Confluence and JIRA for product management

Dear Forum Owners,

We are switching to a new newsletter schedule by delivering more timely updates as well as keeping each update more condensed and to the point. Let's get started!

Tapatalk Monetization - An Updated Dashboard, More Countries, and eCPM Details Explained

Our updated Monetization Dashboard is live! Notable features include:
- A clearer presentation of month to date earnings for your forum.
- A projected estimate what your forum is on track to earn for the current month.
- Tracking of any forgone earnings, so you never miss out on any earning potential.

Note: Impressions generated by countries outside of the US are be paid out at their own local eCPM rates which may vary. We're proud to announce that monetization opportunies have been rolled out to more countries! They now include: United States, United Kingdom, Australia, Italy, Spain, and Germany.  Impressions from within the US will still be paid out at $1.50*, however when combined with impressions from other countries, a lower average eCPM will result.

*$1.50 promotional eCPM for US impressions expires December 31st 2014

Introducing: Forum Homepages - Forums Get a Facelift This Fall on Tapatalk

Upcoming releases of Tapatalk will allow forum owners to take advantage of a new in-app visual customization for their forums.

Each forum will have a homepage that features the forum's logo as well a cover photo. It wonât be long before you can upload your cover photos to the forum owners control panel so stay tuned!  More information can be found at https://sendy.tapatalk.com/l/lnf9dWOFRUETRyOdKyBf8Q/qpHeGcfK67QZB4xIMe763Img/aP892etJrVEoEc7K0BB2ssIQ

Thank You,

The Tapatalk Team

Atlassian
http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdfa15777361067d761d7176&ls=fded13757660017a72107677&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec1167872600d7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff921c75&t= 

Webinar: Using JIRA and Stash for Development Bliss 
Learn how to integrate JIRA and Stash to optimize your development workflow

http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdf415777361067d761c7670&ls=fded13757660017a72107677&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec1167872600d7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff921c75&t= 

November 20 
Thursday, 10am PST

Context switching is tough for development teams of all sizes. In most development workflows, issue trackers like JIRA help track which features have been built, bugs fixed, and outline the roadmap for future releases. Version control systems like Git house the implementation of these issues and let you track the code used to bring these bug fixes and features to life. While both are vital to your development workflow, it's important these systems don't detract from developer productivity and the focus remains on the work at hand.
Join us as we look at integrating JIRA with Stash to optimize your development workflow using Git, and at the same time, provide deeper insight into your work.

In this presentation you'll learn about:
- Designing a Git branching structure for rapid development, painless releases, and simpler issue tracking
- Providing richer context around your work through displaying commits, branches, and pull requests inline with your issues (and vice versa)
- Mapping source code events (like branch creation and pull request merges) to JIRA's powerful workflow triggers, saving developers time and ensuring your issues reflect the reality of your codebase
- Quickly correlating issues, fix versions, and code to take the tedium out of reconciling a release

				<tr>

			<a href="http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdf715777361067d761c7677&ls=fded13757660017a72107677&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec1167872600d7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff921c75&t=" style="text-decoration:none; color: #205081" >Webinar: Using JIRA and Stash for Development Bliss</a></td>
				</tr> 
<!-- end headline -->
<!-- start subheadline -->
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" style="padding-top: 20px; font-family:Helvetica neue, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; color: #707070; font-size: 20px; line-height: 32px; text-align:center; font-weight:none;" align="middle">
				Learn how to integrate JIRA and Stash to optimize your development workflow		</td>
				</tr> 
<!-- end subheadline -->

<!-- start calendar -->
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" style="padding-top: 30px;" align="center">
						<a href="http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdf515777361067d761c7671&ls=fded13757660017a72107677&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec1167872600d7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff921c75&t=" style="text-decoration:none; color: #205081" >
						<table width="265px" align="center" bgcolor="#f5f5f5">
							<tr>
								<td valign="top" style="padding-top: 10px; font-family:Helvetica neue, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; color: #707070; font-size: 32px; line-height: 40px; text-align:center; font-weight:normal;" align="middle">
									November
								</td>
							</tr> 
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" style="padding-top: 10px; padding-bottom:10px;">
						<table width="238px" align="center" bgcolor="#ffffff">
							<tr>
								<td valign="top" style="padding-top: 5px; font-family:Helvetica neue, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; color: #205081; font-size: 120px; line-height: 120px; text-align:center; font-weight:bold;" align="middle">
									20             
								</td>
				 			</tr> 
				 			<tr>
					 			<td valign="top" style="padding-top:5px;padding-bottom:15px;font-family:Helvetica neue, Helvetica, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; color: #707070; font-size: 21px; line-height: 40px; text-align:center; font-weight:normal;" align="middle">
				Thursday, 10am PST

						</table>
					</td>
				</tr>
					</table></a>
				</td>

<!-- end calendar -->
<!-- start body --> 			
				<tr>
					
<td valign="top" style="padding-top: 30px; font-family: Helvetica, Helvetica neue, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; color: #333333; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; text-align:left; font-weight:none;" align="left">Context switching is tough for development teams of all sizes. In most development workflows, issue trackers like JIRA help track which features have been built, bugs fixed, and outline the roadmap for future releases. Version control systems like Git house the implementation of these issues and let you track the code used to bring these bug fixes and features to life. While both are vital to your development workflow, it's important these systems don't detract from developer
 productivity and the focus remains on the work at hand.												</td>
				</tr> 
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" style="padding-top: 10px; font-family: Helvetica, Helvetica neue, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; color: #333333; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; text-align:left; font-weight:none;" align="left">Join us as we look at integrating JIRA with Stash to optimize your development workflow using Git, and at the same time, provide deeper insight into your work.
																</td>
				</tr>
				<tr>
					<td valign="top" style="padding-top: 10px; font-family: Helvetica, Helvetica neue, Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; color: #333333; font-size: 14px; line-height: 20px; text-align:left; font-weight:none;" align="left">In this presentation you'll learn about:
							<ul>
								<li>Designing a Git branching structure for rapid development, painless releases, and simpler issue tracking</li>
								<li style="padding-top:5px;">Providing richer context around your work through displaying commits, branches, and pull requests inline with your issues (and vice versa)</li>
								<li style="padding-top:5px;">Mapping source code events (like branch creation and pull request merges) to JIRA's powerful workflow triggers, saving developers time and ensuring your issues reflect the reality of your codebase</li>
								<li style="padding-top:5px;">Quickly correlating issues, fix versions, and code to take the tedium out of reconciling a release</li>
		</td>
				</tr>

http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdf415777d67017a76167577&ls=fded13757660017a72107677&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec1167872600d7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff941679&t= 

JIRA Agile webinar: How to Deliver Quality Assurance at Speed:
http://click.mailer.atlassian.com/?ju=fdf315777d67017a76167576&ls=fded13757660017a72107677&m=fec2157377620c74&l=fec1167872600d7d&s=fdf31570776c077a7412787d&jb=ff941679&t= 

December 9
Tuesday, 11am PST

Many teams struggle with traditional testing methods in an methods in an agile culture; they feel forced to trade off the quality of their product for the speed of shipping.
Meet Penny Wyatt, leader of the JIRA QA team. She'll walk you through how JIRA enables our developers to be great champions for quality in an agile environment. She will also focus on three key areas to help maximize your development speed without sacrificing quality.

Join us to learn about:
- Creating a culture of quality
- Pushing responsibility for testing back to developers
- Preventing bugs, not detecting them

Michal Kujalowicz, JIRA QA team leader in Gdansk, will be joining Penny for Q&A.

EVE Online: What are your reasons?


Dear da_las,

We've noticed your EVE Online account has not been active lately. If you stopped playing, we would like to learn what were your reasons for leaving. Please take this survey to help us to improve our service. It will only take 5 minutes to complete.

Your participation in this survey is completely voluntary; however, we'd be grateful if you could give us your feedback.

Your survey responses will remain confidential and data from this research will be reported only in the aggregate. If you have questions at any time about the survey, you may contact the research team at the email address survey@eveonline.com mailto:survey@eveonline.com.

Thank you very much for your time and support, and you are always welcome back.

Please start the survey now http://links.mail.eveonline.com/ctt?kn=1&ms=NDEwMDI1NTAS1&r=MTE2NDAyNzAyNzMzS0&b=2&j=NTYzMTMyOTg0S0&mt=1&rt=0.

CCP Research Team

** BuildMaster 4.5 has shipped!
------------------------------------------------------------

In this version (http://inedo.com/buildmaster/4.5?utm_source=3DInedo&utm_c=
ampaign=3D122d2a5acd-MCBuildMaster45&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_term=3D0_b0117=
0860f-122d2a5acd-419655101) our main goal was to make application co=
nfiguration file management a bit easier:
* New Configuration File Editor including syntax highlighting and autocomp=
lete for XML configuration files
* Configuration File Transforms with key/value pair templates or new XSLT
* Compare differences of arbitrary file instances and versions
* Assign a specific version to a release=2C or always deploy the latest

There's a few other changes as well=2C so make sure to check out the relea=
se notes (http://inedo.com/buildmaster/4.5?utm_source=3DInedo&utm_campaign=
=3D122d2a5acd-MCBuildMaster45&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_term=3D0_b01170860f-1=
22d2a5acd-419655101) to learn more.

------------------------------------------------------------

As of January 1st=2C 2015=2C ProGet's license fees will increase across th=
e board (http://inedo.com/proget/pricing/detailed?utm_source=3DInedo&utm_c=
ampaign=3D122d2a5acd-MCBuildMaster45&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_term=3D0_b0117=
0860f-122d2a5acd-419655101) =2C with our basic=2C single-server annu=
al license going from $395 to $595. This is necessary in part due to the m=
ajor changes Microsoft is planning for NuGet 3.0 (http://blog.nuget.org/20=
141112/nuget-3.0-preview.html?utm_source=3DInedo&utm_campaign=3D122d2a5acd=
-MCBuildMaster45&utm_medium=3Demail&utm_term=3D0_b01170860f-122d2a5acd-=
419655101) =2C but also because we're adding a lot more features in as=
 well. We realize this isn't the best news=2C but we'll do our best to acc=
ommodate our existing customers.

e increase=2C please let us know (http://inedo.com/contact?utm_source=3DIn=
